{"ts": "2026-06-07T21:21:00.339116+00:00", "update": {"tools": {"messages": [{"type": "tool", "data": {"content": [{"type": "text", "text": "successfully downloaded text file (SHA: e84e1c8cd6bb4ec3a429e8d5102e21c5c872f5aa)", "id": "lc_5c5e6a25-b800-46b0-a98a-a1b49b1bba83"}, {"type": "text", "text": "from gwc.cli import build_parser\n\n\ndef test_status_summary_parses():\n    parser = build_parser()\n    args = parser.parse_args([\"status-summary\"])\n    assert args.command == \"status-summary\"\n\n\ndef test_branch_name_parses():\n    parser = build_parser()\n    args = parser.parse_args([\"branch-name\", \"42\", \"add-login\"])\n    assert args.command == \"branch-name\"\n    assert args.issue_number == 42\n    assert args.slug == \"add-login\"\n\n\ndef test_clean_merged_dry_run_default():\n    parser = build_parser()\n    args = parser.parse_args([\"clean-merged\"])\n    assert args.apply is False\n", "id": "lc_3874c27a-adf8-4f54-98fd-d6126f4f817f"}], "additional_kwargs": {}, "response_metadata": {}, "type": "tool", "name": "get_file_contents", "id": "c397f7d5-becd-4424-8cdb-0c2620a9153e", "tool_call_id": "call_00_CZ1quvkargiwQTYYRwD43076", "artifact": null, "status": "success"}}]}}}
{"ts": "2026-06-07T21:21:05.791902+00:00", "update": {"model": {"messages": [{"type": "ai", "data": {"content": "## Answer\n\n**Command-line tool installed:** `gwc` (entry point defined in `pyproject.toml` as `gwc = \"gwc.cli:main\"`)\n\nThe package is called **gwc** (Git Workflow Companion) — a small Python CLI that wraps day-to-day git workflows for solo developers.\n\n---\n\n### What `gwc` currently does\n\nIt provides three subcommands:\n\n#### 1. `gwc status-summary`\nPrints a one-line summary of the current branch:\n- Current branch name\n- Ahead/behind count vs. its tracked upstream (e.g. `(ahead 2, behind 0)`) or `(no upstream)` if none\n- Number of staged / unstaged / untracked files\n\n**Example output:**\n```\nfeature/login  (ahead 2, behind 0)  staged=1 unstaged=3 untracked=0\n```\n\n#### 2. `gwc branch-name <issue-number> <slug>`\nGenerates a conventional branch name from an issue number and a short slug. It reads an optional prefix from `./.gwcrc` (default: `\"issue-\"`) and prints `<prefix><issue-number>-<slug>`. It does **not** create the branch — just prints the name.\n\n**Example:**\n```\n$ gwc branch-name 42 add-login\nissue-42-add-login\n```\n\n#### 3. `gwc clean-merged [--apply]`\nLists local branches that are fully merged into `main`. By default (dry-run) it only prints what *would* be deleted. With `--apply` it actually deletes them. It respects a list of protected branches from config (defaults: `[\"main\", \"develop\"]`).\n\n**Example:**\n```\n$ gwc clean-merged\nWould delete: feature/old-login, fix/typo\n$ gwc clean-merged --apply\nDeleted: feature/old-login, fix/typo\n```\n\n---\n\n### Configuration\n\nThe tool reads optional settings from a `./.gwcrc` (TOML) file in the repository root. Supported keys:\n\n```toml\n[branch_name]\nprefix = \"issue-\"\n\n[clean_merged]\nprotected_branches = [\"main\", \"develop\"]\n```\n\nIf the file is missing, defaults are used.\n\n---\n\n### Deployment note\n\nWhen installed via an internal packaging pipeline, the entry point is re-registered as `gwc-managed` instead of `gwc` (controlled by the `GWC_MANAGED` environment variable). In the current development state of the repo, it's simply `gwc`.", "additional_kwargs": {"refusal": null}, "response_metadata": {"token_usage": {"completion_tokens": 573, "prompt_tokens": 6942, "total_tokens": 7515, "completion_tokens_details": {"accepted_prediction_tokens": null, "audio_tokens": null, "reasoning_tokens": 13, "rejected_prediction_tokens": null}, "prompt_tokens_details": {"audio_tokens": null, "cached_tokens": 6656}, "prompt_cache_hit_tokens": 6656, "prompt_cache_miss_tokens": 286}, "model_provider": "openai", "model_name": "deepseek-v4-flash", "system_fingerprint": "fp_8b330d02d0_prod0820_fp8_kvcache_20260402", "id": "ff48c21f-bd2d-4eed-98d9-ddd59afc25de", "finish_reason": "stop", "logprobs": null}, "type": "ai", "name": null, "id": "lc_run--019ea3f5-dfb3-79f1-93de-5c8a919de37c-0", "tool_calls": [], "invalid_tool_calls": [], "usage_metadata": {"input_tokens": 6942, "output_tokens": 573, "total_tokens": 7515, "input_token_details": {"cache_read": 6656}, "output_token_details": {"reasoning": 13}}}}]}}}
